        </div>
        <div class="problem-item">
          <span class="problem-num">ii</span>
          <h3>Product-first, brand-last</h3>
          <p>Most furniture websites lead with product grids and pricing. Brand story, material philosophy and design process — the things that actually justify a premium price — are buried or absent entirely.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="problem-item">
          <span class="problem-num">iii</span>
          <h3>No content system</h3>
          <p>Websites that cannot be updated without a developer become stale within months. New collections do not get launched. Press coverage is not added. The site stops working as a marketing tool.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="problem-item">
          <span class="problem-num">iv</span>
          <h3>Poor SEO architecture</h3>
          <p>Furniture brands invest in beautiful photography but neglect the semantic structure, page speed and metadata that determine whether that investment reaches anyone through search.</p>
